## Location 3 — SECURE (for reference)
### `FeedMediaDispatcher` / `Path.java` — Well-Protected by Regex Validation
**File:** `src/main/java/org/olat/modules/webFeed/dispatching/Path.java`
All URL path components are validated against strict compiled regex patterns before any file operation:
```java
private static final String NUMBER    = "(\\d+)";          // digits only
private static final String WORD      = "(\\w+)";          // alphanum + underscore only
private static final String FILE_NAME = "([^/]+\\.\\w{3,4})"; // no slashes, requires extension
```
The `FILE_NAME` pattern `([^/]+\\.\\w{3,4})` blocks `/` characters entirely, making `../` traversal impossible. The path must fully match one of 12 compiled patterns or an `InvalidPathException` is thrown and the request is rejected. **This location is NOT vulnerable.**"
